name: Beginner Full Body Program
description: A 4-week program designed for beginners to build strength and fitness

workouts.tips: Focus on form over weight. Rest 2-3 minutes between sets.
Keep your core tight during all exercises.
Warm up properly before heavy lifts.

name: Intermediate Push-Pull-Legs
description: A 6-week program using the PPL split for intermediate lifters

workouts.tips: Progressive overload is key. Try to increase weight or reps each week.
Focus on the mind-muscle connection during pulling movements.
Don't skip leg day! These are the foundation of your strength.

name: Core Strength Program
description: A 2-week program focusing on building core strength and stability

workouts.tips: Keep your core engaged during all exercises.
Focus on compound movements that engage the core.

name: Strength and Conditioning
description: A 4-week program combining strength training with conditioning

workouts.tips: Focus on compound movements for maximum efficiency.
Include both pushing and pulling movements.
Focus on proper form to prevent injury.
A strong core is the foundation of all movements.

name: Muscle Building Split
description: A 6-week program designed for muscle hypertrophy

workouts.tips: Focus on the eccentric (lowering) portion of each rep.
Squeeze at the top of each rep for maximum muscle activation.
Progressive overload is key for muscle growth.
Vary your rep ranges to target different muscle fibers.
